         hint while two random gallery thumbnails sit just below it
         as a visual cue. Kept short so it scans cleanly at the small
         caption text style. -->
    <string name="main_send_waiting">Waiting for files…</string>

    <!-- Content description for the two photo preview cards on the
         Send/Receive tab. Generic — the cards rotate through random
         gallery picks so a per-photo description is not feasible. -->
    <string name="main_send_preview_photo_description">Recent gallery photo preview</string>

    <!-- Launcher activity (#34). The "always visible" override lets the
         user force the receiver to publish mDNS even when no BLE pulse is
         in flight — useful when BLE scan is unavailable or the user just
         wants to be discoverable to nearby senders. -->
    <string name="main_always_visible_title">Always visible</string>
    <string name="main_always_visible_subtitle">Keep this device discoverable on Wi-Fi even without a Bluetooth pulse from a nearby sender. Turn off to save power; the receiver will only appear briefly while a sender is scanning.</string>
    <!-- OFF-state label for the always-visible pill on the Send/Receive
         tab. Phrased as the inverse of the ON-state title so the same
         button reads as a clear two-position switch: ON = "Always
         visible", OFF = "Visible on scan" (i.e. only when a sender's
         BLE pulse wakes the receiver). -->
    <string name="main_always_visible_off_title">Visible on scan</string>
    <!-- Captions rendered just below the always-visible pill, outside
         the button silhouette. Swapped per pill state so the user
         sees a plain-language summary of what the current state
         actually means:
           * ON  ("Always visible")     → anyone nearby can share.
           * OFF ("Visible on scan")    → discoverability only fires
             while a nearby device is actively scanning over BLE.
         The fragment swaps the caption in lockstep with the pill's
         label / background in `refreshVisibilityButton`. -->
    <string name="main_always_visible_caption_on">Anyone nearby can share files with me.</string>
    <string name="main_always_visible_caption_off">Active only while a nearby device is scanning over Bluetooth.</string>
    <string name="main_bug_report_title">Shake to report a bug</string>
    <string name="main_bug_report_subtitle">When enabled, shaking the phone while Bada is open offers to package recent diagnostics, device state, and a screenshot into a zip that you save yourself. Nothing is uploaded automatically.</string>

